  "instructions": [
    "Heat the render-fat in a large cast-iron skillet over medium-high heat until it reaches 375°F.",
    "Add the diced ham and cook until browned, about 3-4 minutes.",
    "Add the grated ginger and cook for an additional 1-2 minutes.",
    "Stir in the fromage frais until melted and well combined with the ham and ginger mixture.",
    "Add the grated cheddar cheese and stir until melted and smooth.",
    "Transfer the skillet to the oven and bake at 375°F for 10-12 minutes, or until the cheese is melted and bubbly.",
    "Remove the skillet from the oven and sprinkle with sliced scallions and grated cilantro."
